has strong hazard anticipation and leadership but health and organization issues. B handles stress well but interpersonal issues. C quick decisions but communication issues.\n\nGiven long-distance flights require calmness under pressure (B has that), teamwork (none strong), decision-making (A, C, D have some). I think B's stress handling is a strong point, but his uncooperative nature is concerning. D's problem solving and responsibility are strong, but moodiness may affect crew. A's leadership is good but health and organization issues could be problematic. C's communication issues are big.\n\nThus maybe D still best overall, but we need to consider missing info. I will vote Candidate D, aligning with Agent 3, but note that we still lack info.\n\nThus produce public message: answer the four questions (lack of info) and maybe summarize our view, and vote D.\n\nMake sure metadata: agent \"agent_1\", vote \"Candidate D\"."}
